message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper deals with Named Entity Recognition (NER) using external knowledge and formulates it as a multi-answer question answering (MAQA) task. This involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which are associated with the sub-category of cs.IR. Finally, the paper deals with Named Entities (NE), which is a specific area of NLP and ML, and is associated with the sub-category of cs.NE.
